--- New scetch of memo system & instruction set 

Instructions:
    MATCH       x,y         - Push 'true' if x <= input <= y
    CALL        <ADDR>      - Call regardless of state
    CALL.IT     <ADDR>      - Call if 'true'
    CALL.NT     <ADDR>      - Call if not 'false'
    CALL.M        <ADDR>    - Call regardless of state, do a memo lookup
    CALL.IT.M   <ADDR>      - Call if 'true', do a memo lookup
    CALL.NT.M   <ADDR>      - Call if 'false', do a memo lookup
    RET.RES                 - Return, and generate a result, no memoization
    RET.1                   - Return, generate a result from one state, memoize
    RET.2                   - Return, generate a result from two states, memomize


The Parser:
    digit ::= '0' - '9'
    number ::= digit + number | digit

The Compilation
    digitParser:
        MATCH   '0', '9'
        RET.1
    
    digitResultParser:
        CALL.M  digitParser
        RET.1

    numberParser:
        CALL.M      numberParserSeq
        CALL.NT.M   digitParser
        RET.2

    numberParserSeq:
        CALL.M      digitParser
        CALL.TR.M   numberParser
        RET.2